eqSonetMib.name: eqSonetMib
eqSonetMib.contactinfo: Jas Parmar Equipe Communications 100 Nagog Park Acton MA 01720
eqSonetMib.description: This is the Equipe SONET MIB module.

EqSonetApsCfgStatus.name: EqSonetApsCfgStatus
EqSonetApsCfgStatus.description: Equipe sonet aps config status values.

EqSonetApsCfgAction.name: EqSonetApsCfgAction
EqSonetApsCfgAction.description: Equipe sonet aps config action values.

eqSonetApsCfgTable.name: eqSonetApsCfgTable
eqSonetApsCfgTable.description: This table contains aps config info for a sonet port.

eqSonetApsCfgEntry.name: eqSonetApsCfgEntry
eqSonetApsCfgEntry.description: A sonet port aps config entry.

eqSonetApsCfgStatus.name: eqSonetApsCfgStatus
eqSonetApsCfgStatus.description: The current aps status for this sonet port.

eqSonetApsCfgAction.name: eqSonetApsCfgAction
eqSonetApsCfgAction.description: This object is used to perform an aps action on a sonet port. A read on this object always returns the value other(1). Setting this object to clear(2) causes the port to revert back to default aps configuration. Setting this object to lockoutProtecting(3) prevents any of the working channels from switching to the protecting line. Setting this object to forcedSwitchWorkingToProtecting(4) switches the working port to the protecting port. Setting this object to forcedSwitchProtectingToWorking(5) switches the protecting port to the working port. Setting this object to manualSwitchWorkingToProtecting(6) switches the working port to the protecting port. Setting this object to manualSwitchProtectingToWorking(7) switches the protecting port to the working port.

eqSonetApsCfgLastAction.name: eqSonetApsCfgLastAction
eqSonetApsCfgLastAction.description: This object indicates the last aps action requested on this port.

eqSonetApsCfgPortActive.name: eqSonetApsCfgPortActive
eqSonetApsCfgPortActive.description: This object is used to determine if the sts paths configured on this port are currrently actually terminated on this port. This is used to determine if the port is in active or standby mode. A value of false(1) indicates that the sts paths are not terminated (standby). A value of true(2) indicates that the sts paths are terminated (active).

eqSonetPathTable.name: eqSonetPathTable
eqSonetPathTable.description: This table contains config info for a sonet port.

eqSonetPathActualPort.name: eqSonetPathActualPort
eqSonetPathActualPort.description: The ifIndex of the sonet port over which this path is actually running. Note that this value could be different from the sonet port that the sts path was originally configured.

eqSonetStatsTable.name: eqSonetStatsTable
eqSonetStatsTable.description: This table contains stats for a sonet port.

eqSonetStatsIfIndex.name: eqSonetStatsIfIndex
eqSonetStatsIfIndex.description: The ifIndex for the corresponding sonet port.

eqSonetStatsLineFailures.name: eqSonetStatsLineFailures
eqSonetStatsLineFailures.description: The number of line failure events. A line failure is an AIS-L signal received from another NE, or received from the same NE when internally generating an AIS-L signal in the LTE.

eqSonetStatsLineApsCount.name: eqSonetStatsLineApsCount
eqSonetStatsLineApsCount.description: The number of times the service has switched from the working to the protect line.

eqSonetStatsLineApsSwitchDuration.name: eqSonetStatsLineApsSwitchDuration
eqSonetStatsLineApsSwitchDuration.description: The number of seconds the service has been carried on the protection line.

eqSonetStatsLineStsPtrAdjustments.name: eqSonetStatsLineStsPtrAdjustments
eqSonetStatsLineStsPtrAdjustments.description: The count of STS pointer adjustments created or absorbed by an NE due to differences in the frame rates of the incoming and outgoing sonet signal.

eqSonetStatsPathFailures.name: eqSonetStatsPathFailures
eqSonetStatsPathFailures.description: The number of path failure events. A path failure is an AIS-P signal received from another NE, or received from the same NE when internally generating an AIS-P signal in the PTE. A path with support for ERDI-P will increment this counter when an UNEQ-P failure is declared.

eqSonetStatsTimeElapsed.name: eqSonetStatsTimeElapsed
eqSonetStatsTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the current measurement period. If, for some reason, such as an adjustment in the system's time-of-day clock, the current interval exceeds the maximum value, the agent will return the maximum value.
